Question Given two integers M & N, calculate and return their multiplication using recursion. You can only use subtraction and addition for your calculation. 
No other operators are allowed.

CODE;

public class solution {

	static int sum = 0;
	public static int multiplyTwoIntegers(int m, int n){
	if(n==0)return sum;

	return sum+m+multiplyTwoIntegers(m,n-1);
}
}
